---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Control Plane API Docs</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="min-h-screen bg-[#f7f8fb] px-4 py-8 text-slate-950 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
        <header class="mb-8">
          <p class="mb-3 inline-flex rounded-full border border-slate-200 bg-white px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-600">
            OpenAPI available at /openapi.json
          </p>
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-normal">Control Plane API Docs</h1>
          <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
            Astro supports API routes through files under <code>src/pages</code>,
            but it does not automatically generate Swagger/OpenAPI docs from
            those routes. This page documents the current API manually and links
            to a static OpenAPI description.
          </p>
        </header>

        <section class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-4">
          <a class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 shadow-sm transition hover:border-slate-300" href="/openapi.json">
            <h2 class="text-base font-semibold">OpenAPI JSON</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
              Machine-readable API spec for Swagger UI, Redoc, or client generation.
            </p>
          </a>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-base font-semibold">Auth</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
              Dashboard endpoints use the session cookie. Product API endpoints
              use <code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;api_key&gt;</code>.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-base font-semibold">Metering</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
              API-key calls update <code>last_used_at</code> only when a usage
              event is recorded, and write idempotent usage rows for billing
              aggregation.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-base font-semibold">Billing</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
              Stripe test-mode Checkout creates subscriptions. Local usage rows
              are synced to Stripe meter events for invoice calculation.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-xs leading-5 text-slate-500">
              Full setup runbook: <code>docs/stripe-billing-setup.md</code>
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-8 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm">
          <div class="border-b border-slate-200 p-4">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Use a Minted API Key</h2>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">
              After creating an API key in the dashboard, call the mock endpoint:
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4">
<pre class="overflow-x-auto rounded-md bg-slate-950 p-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-100"><code>curl -sS http://127.0.0.1:4321/api/mock/inference \
  -H 'Authorization: Bearer cp_live_your_key_here' \
  -H 'Idempotency-Key: request_123' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '&#123;"prompt":"Summarize usage for this workspace"&#125;'</code></pre>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-8 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm">
          <div class="border-b border-slate-200 p-4">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Enable Mock Stripe Billing</h2>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">
              Keep Postgres as the usage ledger and use Stripe test mode for
              subscription checkout and invoice metering.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid gap-4 p-4 md:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-md border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">Stripe setup</h3>
              <ol class="mt-3 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-5 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
                <li>Create a test-mode Product and metered recurring Price.</li>
                <li>Create a Billing Meter whose event name matches <code>STRIPE_METER_EVENT_NAME</code>.</li>
                <li>Use default meter payload keys: <code>stripe_customer_id</code> and <code>value</code>.</li>
                <li>Set <code>STRIPE_SECRET_KEY</code>, <code>STRIPE_PRICE_ID</code>, and <code>STRIPE_METER_EVENT_NAME</code>.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-md border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">Webhook setup</h3>
              <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
                Forward Stripe webhooks to the local app and copy the webhook
                signing secret into <code>STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET</code>.
              </p>
<pre class="mt-3 overflow-x-auto rounded-md bg-slate-950 p-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-100"><code>stripe listen \
  --forward-to localhost:4321/api/webhooks/stripe</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-8 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm">
          <div class="border-b border-slate-200 p-4">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Current Endpoints</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full min-w-[760px] text-left text-sm">
              <thead class="bg-slate-50 text-xs uppercase text-slate-500">
                <tr>
                  <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Method</th>
                  <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Path</th>
                  <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Auth</th>
                  <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Purpose</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">POST</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">/api/mock/inference</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Bearer API key</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Mock product endpoint that records idempotent usage.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">POST</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">/api/usage/events</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Bearer API key</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Manually record a structured usage event for an API key.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">GET/POST</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">/api/api-keys</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Session cookie</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">List and mint API keys for the signed-in user.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">PATCH/DELETE</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">/api/api-keys/:id</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Session cookie</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Rename or revoke an API key.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">GET</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">/api/usage</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Session cookie</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Read usage totals for the signed-in user.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">GET</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">/api/billing/status</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Session cookie</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Read Stripe setup, subscription, and meter sync status.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">POST</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">/api/billing/checkout</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Session cookie</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Create a Stripe Checkout subscription session.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">POST</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">/api/billing/portal</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Session cookie</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Create a Stripe Billing Portal session.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">POST</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">/api/webhooks/stripe</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Stripe signature</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Update local subscription state from Stripe webhooks.</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
